.SH NAME
.PP
chmod \- Change the access permissions of a file or directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Give the [u]ser who owns a file the right to e[x]ecute it:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
chmod\ u+x\ {{file}}
\f[]
.fi
.PP
Give the user rights to [r]ead and [w]rite to a file/directory:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
chmod\ u+rw\ {{file}}
\f[]
.fi
.PP
Remove executable rights from the [g]roup:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
chmod\ g\-x\ {{file}}
\f[]
.fi
.PP
Give [a]ll users rights to read and execute:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
chmod\ a+rx\ {{file}}
\f[]
.fi
.PP
Give [o]thers (not in the file owner\[aq]s group) the same rights as the
group:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
chmod\ o=g\ {{file}}
\f[]
.fi
